# Cognito — user pools & identity pools

Two distinct services under one name.

## User Pools — *who are you?*

Managed **user directory**: sign-up / sign-in.

- Email + password, configurable policies
- **Social** (Google, Facebook, Apple) + **enterprise** (SAML, OIDC — Okta, Azure AD)
- **MFA**, verification, **adaptive auth** (risk-based)
- **Hosted UI** — pre-built sign-in page, no login form to build
- Returns **3 JWTs** — ID, access, refresh

## Identity Pools — *what can you reach?*

- Swap a token → **temporary AWS credentials** via STS `AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity`
- Client calls S3 / DynamoDB **directly** — no backend proxy
- **Two IAM roles**: authenticated + unauthenticated (guest); role-based access

**Pairing:** User Pool **authenticates** → Identity Pool **authorises to AWS**.
